INTRODUCTION: The burden of oral cancer is high in Hungary.
AIM: To study the cost-effectiveness of potential oral cancer screening in 
Hungary.
METHOD: Three strategies were compared: no introduction of screening, organized 
yearly screening for 40-year-old males in general medical practise, and 
opportunistic screening of high risk 40-year-old males in primary care. Local 
estimates of health utilities and costs of each health state and of the 
